What's best practice for open access?
The business of publishing journals is in transition. Nobody knows exactly how
	it will work in the future, but everybody knows that the electronic
	publishing revolution will ensure it won't work as it does now. This
	knowledge has provoked a growing sense of nervous anticipation among
	those concerned, some edgy and threatened by potential changes to their
	business, others excited by the prospect of change and opportunity. The
	paper discusses the open publishing model for dissemination of research
